WEBVTT

00:03.237 --> 00:04.905
(Khadijah gasps)

00:04.938 --> 00:06.774
-My baby! No! No!
-SKULLY: You gonna have to get

00:06.807 --> 00:08.276
that hate out your heart.

00:08.309 --> 00:09.743
If it was me that got killed...

00:10.811 --> 00:11.912
...would you forgive?

00:11.912 --> 00:13.681
(gunshot)

00:13.747 --> 00:14.748
LOUIE:
If you kill us now...

00:16.117 --> 00:17.751
...it ain't gonna never end.

00:17.751 --> 00:20.754
Our people gonna come after you

00:20.788 --> 00:22.090
till there ain't nobody left.

00:23.324 --> 00:26.194
Thought we'd start off
with ten keys a week.

00:26.260 --> 00:28.262
You say you wanted to focus
on real estate.

00:28.296 --> 00:29.597
Y'all can't do what I do.

00:29.630 --> 00:31.299
We the ones that made it right
with Skully.

00:31.332 --> 00:35.269
Now we want to run
what's ours our way.

00:35.303 --> 00:36.937
BUCKLEY:
Well, unless you want to go bak

00:36.937 --> 00:39.207
to not having my protection,
I suggest you find

00:39.273 --> 00:40.341
somebody to serve up.

00:41.609 --> 00:43.544
My time now is being
in real estate with you.

00:43.611 --> 00:45.113
Grady's on our side,

00:45.113 --> 00:47.148
in legit business with us.

00:47.181 --> 00:49.117
He don't want anything bad
to happen to us.

00:49.150 --> 00:50.984
You sure you can work
with the asset?

00:51.018 --> 00:52.286
TEDDY: What,
you mean that I saved his ass

00:52.286 --> 00:53.887
with that reporter?

00:53.954 --> 00:55.556
See, I was thinking more
about what you did

00:55.623 --> 00:56.990
to his father in Cuba.

00:57.024 --> 00:58.792
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

00:58.792 --> 01:01.962
HAVEMEYER:
Get Grady in line,
but do it quietly.

01:01.995 --> 01:03.897
FRANKLIN:
Hey, Reed, Grady had agreed
to cut the prices down.

01:03.964 --> 01:05.799
$9,000 a kilo.

01:05.833 --> 01:07.335
I'm hoping you can honor that.

01:07.368 --> 01:09.069
Let's keep it at ten for now.

01:09.137 --> 01:10.971
Also, Reed's gone.

01:10.971 --> 01:12.806
From here on,
you can call me Teddy.

01:21.882 --> 01:24.818
-JEROME: Just like that?
-FRANKLIN: Just like that.

01:24.818 --> 01:26.187
LOUIE:
He say why?

01:28.055 --> 01:30.324
Said Grady was
reckless and wasteful

01:30.358 --> 01:33.161
and putting us all in jeopardy.

01:33.161 --> 01:34.695
And you believe him?

01:34.728 --> 01:36.697
Can't say Grady ran
the tightest ship.

01:36.730 --> 01:39.167
(takes deep breath)

01:39.167 --> 01:41.602
It was bound to hit the rocks
sooner or later.

01:41.669 --> 01:44.172
-What did Grady say?
-I don't know.

01:44.172 --> 01:47.007
His house is empty, and he
ain't answering my pages, so...

01:47.007 --> 01:49.009
JEROME:
So what you saying, nephew?

01:49.009 --> 01:52.213
-You think that Reed killed him?
-Teddy.

01:52.246 --> 01:54.382
-What?
-Said to call him Teddy
from here on out.

01:54.415 --> 01:57.017
And I don't know that, either.

01:57.017 --> 01:58.519
LOUIE:
You think Grady
just walked away

01:58.552 --> 02:00.621
from everything,
all y'all's business,

02:00.688 --> 02:02.856
without so much as a phone call?

02:02.890 --> 02:05.526
I think if the CIA shows up,
tells you it's over

02:05.526 --> 02:08.028
and you got to move on,
then that's exactly what you do.

02:08.061 --> 02:10.464
But yeah,
he could have killed him.

02:10.531 --> 02:12.300
Lions sometimes eat their young.

02:12.366 --> 02:13.967
I just can't think
of a lot of reasons

02:14.034 --> 02:15.369
why Teddy would've had to.

02:15.403 --> 02:17.371
I can. Saw you and Grady
was like Bert and Ernie

02:17.371 --> 02:19.373
-up in this motherfucker.
-(chuckles)

02:19.373 --> 02:20.974
Wanted to send a message
they knew you would hear.

02:21.041 --> 02:22.710
LOUIE:
You mean, in addition

02:22.710 --> 02:24.578
to disappearing his father?

02:24.612 --> 02:26.914
That come up
in your little chat?

02:26.947 --> 02:29.817
Whatever happened to Alton,
he did to himself.

02:29.883 --> 02:31.652
Bottom line is,
whoever the CIA sends,

02:31.719 --> 02:33.221
we got to do business with them.

02:33.221 --> 02:35.055
And that's exactly
what we're gonna do.

02:35.055 --> 02:37.258
Well, we can't do nothin'
without that price cut.

02:37.291 --> 02:40.093
-We still good on that?
-FRANKLIN: (sighs) No.

02:40.127 --> 02:41.229
Teddy's not gonna honor
Grady's word.

02:41.229 --> 02:42.563
Prices stay the same.

02:42.596 --> 02:45.566
I made promises.

02:45.599 --> 02:47.167
Well, you're gonna have
to break 'em.

02:47.235 --> 02:48.902
LOUIE: How about I take Teddy
on a little ride-along?

02:48.936 --> 02:51.839
Let him see how the Colombians
got the game sewed up.

02:51.905 --> 02:53.407
(chuckles)
Yeah, that'll do it.

02:53.441 --> 02:54.675
Me and him,
we did business for months

02:54.742 --> 02:56.076
when you was laid up.

02:56.109 --> 02:57.478
-Let me try and talk to him.
-I'll talk to him.

02:59.280 --> 03:01.349
Till then, y'all
just keep moving these keys.

03:01.415 --> 03:04.452
Now's not the time to tell Teddy
business is falling off.

03:04.485 --> 03:07.321
I'll let you all know more
when I do.

03:08.756 --> 03:10.791
*

03:16.764 --> 03:19.132
(train whistle blowing)

03:19.166 --> 03:22.202
(lighter flicking)

03:22.270 --> 03:24.938
It ain't on us, they don't
like it, they don't like it.

03:24.938 --> 03:27.207
Fuck we gonna do?

03:27.275 --> 03:29.209
(hip hop music playing
over car radio)

03:29.277 --> 03:30.778
(tires squeal)

03:38.452 --> 03:40.187
-(engine shuts off)
-(music stops)

03:50.130 --> 03:52.500
My favorite people.

03:52.533 --> 03:54.802
-Looking well.
-Mello.

03:56.637 --> 03:58.472
What up with you, Mello?

03:58.506 --> 04:01.241
Shit, trying to get like y'all.

04:01.309 --> 04:02.843
You got it, boss.

04:04.211 --> 04:05.746
LOUIE:
Heads up.

04:05.813 --> 04:07.247
Couldn't get that price cut.

04:07.315 --> 04:09.583
It's not a call I could make.

04:09.650 --> 04:11.485
And for that I apologize.

04:13.654 --> 04:14.822
Well, see, now you put me--

04:14.855 --> 04:17.157
us--

04:17.157 --> 04:19.360
in a bad position.

04:19.393 --> 04:22.229
Hey, ease the fuck off
or shit get ugly.

04:23.531 --> 04:25.265
MELLO:
You see...

04:25.333 --> 04:27.267
I like this,

04:27.335 --> 04:29.603
but I'm not in charge.

04:29.670 --> 04:33.841
You know, just like you,
this is not a call I can make.

04:35.075 --> 04:38.846
And now I got to tell the man
who's in charge

04:38.846 --> 04:42.015
that things aren't as you said.

04:42.015 --> 04:45.453
Nah, fuck all that.
They can tell him.

04:45.519 --> 04:49.022
You know Skully; honor, God,
samurais, and fucking spirits.

04:49.056 --> 04:51.359
Oh, he not a fan
of niggas renegin'.

04:51.392 --> 04:53.394
You think there's gonna be
a problem?

04:53.427 --> 04:57.197
(exhales)
I can't call it, big dawg.

04:57.197 --> 04:59.633
You know,
he has good days and...

04:59.700 --> 05:02.470
he has real bad days.

05:02.536 --> 05:05.539
If you've got time,

05:05.573 --> 05:08.108
I'd pray for a good one.

05:13.046 --> 05:14.782
(train whistle blowing
in distance)

05:20.053 --> 05:22.490
(phone ringing)

05:22.556 --> 05:25.225
Ten grand? Yeah, all right.

05:25.258 --> 05:27.260
No, go ahead and do it.

05:27.294 --> 05:29.497
Send the invoice
to the business.

05:29.563 --> 05:31.064
Thanks.

05:33.401 --> 05:36.336
-New windshield.
-For the Cadillac?

05:36.404 --> 05:39.072
-For the plane.
-(laughing)

05:40.741 --> 05:42.175
(whispers):
Right.

05:42.242 --> 05:43.644
Mm-mm.

05:44.945 --> 05:47.080
Looking at me
like I owe you money.

05:47.114 --> 05:48.916
-(chuckles)
-I could you right now
I ain't got it.

05:48.916 --> 05:51.351
What I do got is paperwork.

05:51.419 --> 05:53.421
Your go-ahead for the bid.

05:53.421 --> 05:55.155
Less than 48 hours
to submit, huh?

05:56.424 --> 05:57.691
Yeah.

05:57.758 --> 05:59.693
All right,
I'll go through this tonight.

05:59.760 --> 06:02.430
-Mm-hmm.
-Finish it up tomorrow.

06:02.430 --> 06:05.132
In the meantime, I need you
to do something else for me.

06:05.165 --> 06:08.368
-What you need?
-Uh, we got to put Grady's house
on the market.

06:08.436 --> 06:10.438
(chuckles)

06:10.438 --> 06:12.205
I'm not surprised.

06:12.272 --> 06:14.207
He's got "rolling stone" written
all over him,

06:14.274 --> 06:15.976
and, you know,
they don't gather no moss.

06:16.009 --> 06:18.479
Grady's left town, V.

06:18.512 --> 06:21.815
-He's out.
-Mm.

06:21.849 --> 06:23.784
-(takes deep breath)
-Teddy's back in.

06:23.784 --> 06:25.385
Teddy?

06:25.453 --> 06:26.787
Reed.

06:30.624 --> 06:32.325
When'd this happen?

06:32.359 --> 06:34.127
Last night.

06:36.997 --> 06:38.799
You thought
he wasn't coming back.

06:38.799 --> 06:40.834
I was wrong.

06:42.169 --> 06:45.072
Okay.

06:45.138 --> 06:47.074
Well, did you ask him
about your dad,

06:47.140 --> 06:49.076
if he had anything to do
with it?

06:49.142 --> 06:50.978
Caught me a little off guard.

06:50.978 --> 06:52.813
That definitely wasn't
an accident.

06:59.653 --> 07:02.422
I'm not a mind reader,
so I'm gonna need you to tell me

07:02.490 --> 07:06.159
-how you're feeling, Franklin.
-(sighs)

07:06.159 --> 07:08.328
I think as long
as I've done right by Teddy,

07:08.328 --> 07:09.830
he's had my back.

07:09.863 --> 07:12.866
I asked how you felt,
not what you think.

07:15.503 --> 07:18.338
I don't know right now, babe.

07:18.371 --> 07:21.008
All I know is that he needs me.

07:21.041 --> 07:24.077
As long as I make him money,
we all good.

07:25.513 --> 07:27.848
That's all I got for now,
all right?

07:33.854 --> 07:34.922
(sighs)

07:36.223 --> 07:38.191
Truck outside.
I figured I'd bring it in.

07:38.225 --> 07:41.529
Aw, thank you, baby.
You didn't have to do that.

07:41.529 --> 07:43.797
I know, it's fine.

07:43.864 --> 07:46.900
-I had the time.
-(beeping)

07:49.269 --> 07:51.705
(sighs)

07:51.705 --> 07:54.908
Proverbs 25:14.

07:56.544 --> 07:59.146
A man that promises a gift

07:59.212 --> 08:01.749
and doesn't give
is like clouds...

08:01.782 --> 08:03.651
I'm guessing y'all ain't pray
for that good day.

08:03.717 --> 08:05.218
How bad?

08:05.218 --> 08:07.320
Tianna's-birthday-tomorrow bad.

08:07.387 --> 08:09.256
SKULLY:
Niggas need to see

08:09.289 --> 08:13.561
they consequences in action.

08:13.561 --> 08:15.162
He'd like to see you.

08:15.228 --> 08:16.964
-Now.
-(line clicks off)

08:20.934 --> 08:22.570
How much you hear?

08:22.603 --> 08:26.774
-Sounded like Old Testament
this time.
-Fuck.

08:33.146 --> 08:34.815
-(dog barking in distance)
-(man whistles)

08:36.750 --> 08:38.786
(siren wailing in distance)

08:41.488 --> 08:42.790
MAN:
Yo!

08:47.928 --> 08:50.798
You think this is a fucking
joke? This shit is for real.

08:50.831 --> 08:53.100
You don't fuck with the Bible,
motherfuckers.

08:53.133 --> 08:54.702
* And move your feet
to the beat *

08:54.768 --> 08:57.104
* And the feeling gets
much better *

08:57.104 --> 08:58.772
-* When you're feeling
the heat *
-(baby crying in distance)

08:58.806 --> 09:01.709
*

09:01.775 --> 09:04.945
* So get on up *

09:04.978 --> 09:06.814
*

09:08.015 --> 09:09.950
(door opens)

09:13.186 --> 09:16.056
I wouldn't bring heat
to the fire.

09:16.123 --> 09:18.826
I got enough heat to toast
this motherfucker if I need.

09:21.128 --> 09:22.195
(chuckles softly)

09:30.804 --> 09:32.472
* We're shakin' up
the party... *

09:32.472 --> 09:34.174
The fuck, homie?

09:34.207 --> 09:35.976
Hey, look, I ain't even
the nigga that lied.

09:35.976 --> 09:38.078
It was them marked-ass niggas.

09:38.145 --> 09:40.681
SKULLY:
False words, real consequences.

09:40.714 --> 09:42.750
CORNROWS:
No! (screaming)

09:42.816 --> 09:44.184
Fuck! Oh!

09:44.217 --> 09:46.186
-(yelling)
-Calm down, nigga.

09:46.219 --> 09:48.155
Shut up. Get your ass up

09:48.188 --> 09:49.990
and get that blood off my floor.

09:50.023 --> 09:52.993
It's over.
Listen close next time.

09:52.993 --> 09:55.095
Get this nigga out of here.

09:55.162 --> 09:57.698
(wailing in pain)

09:57.731 --> 10:01.835
And make sure he don't bleed
all over my baby's balloons.

10:03.070 --> 10:06.539
Thought we was on another plane.

10:06.573 --> 10:09.843
Thought we transcended
this bullshit.

10:09.877 --> 10:13.180
Now y'all want to sell me
wolf tickets again?

10:13.180 --> 10:14.848
What happened to the honor?

10:14.848 --> 10:16.850
Our business with you is
our honor.

10:16.850 --> 10:18.218
Our loyalty.

10:18.251 --> 10:20.520
Lying to me
ain't no motherfucking loyalty.

10:20.553 --> 10:22.222
LOUIE:
We didn't lie to you.

10:22.255 --> 10:25.859
We were told one thing,
then we were told another.

10:25.893 --> 10:28.195
-It's out of our hands.
-SKULLY: You know,

10:28.228 --> 10:29.963
Titi is in here.

10:30.030 --> 10:33.366
I ain't even supposed
to be carrying on like this.

10:33.400 --> 10:35.635
Ten a key--
that's what you said,

10:35.703 --> 10:39.239
-and that's what it's gonna be.
-Skully, we can't do that.

10:39.272 --> 10:40.874
SKULLY:
Man, you can do that!

10:40.874 --> 10:42.242
'Cause you said and you owe me.

10:42.275 --> 10:44.544
-You already know that.
-LOUIE: Okay.

10:44.544 --> 10:46.213
We'll do it.

10:46.213 --> 10:48.215
Daddy's sorry, baby.

10:48.215 --> 10:50.050
I don't mean to get loud.

10:51.284 --> 10:54.587
Hit y'all up later
to reschedule the drop

10:54.621 --> 10:56.556
after I deal with this shit.

11:00.093 --> 11:03.230
SKULLY: You know,
possums smell like shit

11:03.230 --> 11:06.399
when they tricking predators
into thinking they dead.

11:06.433 --> 11:08.168
But the smart ones

11:08.235 --> 11:11.604
don't play with
the same predator over and over,

11:11.638 --> 11:14.274
because they afraid he
might become wise to the smell.

11:14.307 --> 11:17.410
Did you smell anything on them?

11:17.444 --> 11:19.579
As in possum shit?

11:19.579 --> 11:23.616
As in, do what you say
and say what you mean,

11:23.650 --> 11:26.253
or you can't be trusted.

11:26.253 --> 11:28.521
-He comin' apart.
-With expenses,

11:28.588 --> 11:30.623
we out at least a few hundo
every bird we sell to him.

11:30.657 --> 11:33.093
We in business with a madman,

11:33.126 --> 11:35.095
and we ain't even making money
doing it.

11:35.128 --> 11:38.766
Way he goin',
ain't gonna be long.

11:38.766 --> 11:40.768
We can wait him out,
let him implode,

11:40.768 --> 11:42.970
wait for the next man to rise.

11:44.271 --> 11:45.438
I see your wheels turning.

11:45.438 --> 11:47.107
You notice Mello?

11:47.107 --> 11:49.276
-Itching.
-Uh-huh.

11:49.276 --> 11:50.811
We can use that.

12:17.805 --> 12:19.807
(traffic passing)

12:40.828 --> 12:42.195
(children chattering, laughing)

12:42.229 --> 12:43.897
Come on.

12:45.365 --> 12:47.000
-(school bell ringing)
-Come on, come on. We late.

12:53.841 --> 12:55.042
(car door closes)

12:56.343 --> 12:57.878
Come on.

12:59.179 --> 13:01.181
Wrong place to start some drama.

13:01.214 --> 13:03.350
Girl, ain't no drama.

13:05.052 --> 13:07.054
Y'all know Mello?

13:07.087 --> 13:08.856
Skully's boy.

13:08.856 --> 13:11.458
-Hey.
-Who don't?
He stay in the streets.

13:11.524 --> 13:13.460
Saw him yesterday buying
some Jordans at the Fox Hills.

13:13.526 --> 13:15.963
I heard he hang tough
over where y'all used to dance.

13:16.029 --> 13:18.231
-First Kings.
-BLACK DIAMOND: Used to?

13:18.265 --> 13:20.200
Nah. We can't gamble
feeding these babies

13:20.233 --> 13:23.070
-on no damn dope money.
-Might not always be sufficient.

13:23.103 --> 13:25.238
Well, we need somebody
to slide in his ear,

13:25.272 --> 13:29.042
-remind him of his potential.
-Y'all steady playing us
to the left.

13:29.042 --> 13:31.078
Maybe we just shoot you
in the stomach.

13:31.111 --> 13:33.546
-Play a game of spades after.
-BLACK DIAMOND: Look, I thought
we was past that

13:33.546 --> 13:35.648
-when y'all brought us on.
-You think I brought you on?

13:35.715 --> 13:37.650
If it was up to me...

13:37.717 --> 13:39.586
-We'd be dead. Right?
-DALLAS: Man, come on.

13:39.619 --> 13:42.222
why you bringing up old shit?

13:42.222 --> 13:44.257
We've been hospitable
as fuck since.

13:44.291 --> 13:46.059
-You stay trippin'.
-LOUIE: Call us past it

13:46.059 --> 13:47.660
if you help us out.

13:47.727 --> 13:49.729
You know somebody to do it?

13:51.598 --> 13:53.833
Puff The Magic Dragon.

13:53.901 --> 13:55.635
-JEROME: Who?
-We'll set it up.

13:57.237 --> 13:58.471
Come on, baby.

13:59.940 --> 14:04.277
(sighs)
Little late for this, but...

14:04.311 --> 14:06.579
I'm sorry for...

14:06.579 --> 14:08.748
shooting you and all.

14:09.950 --> 14:12.252
I'm glad you didn't not make it.

14:16.323 --> 14:18.458
I did it again.

14:18.491 --> 14:20.093
-(school bell ringing)
-BLACK DIAMOND: You gonna
be a good boy?

14:32.105 --> 14:33.941
Morning. Listen, um...

14:38.946 --> 14:41.114
FRANKLIN:
Had them get you some coffee.

14:41.114 --> 14:41.949
Okay.

14:43.450 --> 14:44.784
Thank you.

14:48.121 --> 14:49.789
(sighs)

14:50.790 --> 14:52.692
Stopped smoking, huh?

14:58.198 --> 15:01.168
So, I thought
maybe we should talk.

15:01.201 --> 15:03.903
Caught me a little off guard
the other day.

15:03.971 --> 15:05.305
So what?
So anything in particular

15:05.305 --> 15:06.673
-you want to talk about?
-Well, you know, I...

15:06.706 --> 15:09.076
For starters, I hate
to beat a dead horse here,

15:09.142 --> 15:11.078
but I think
maybe I wasn't clear

15:11.144 --> 15:12.645
about why that price cut's
so important.

15:12.645 --> 15:14.081
Oh, no, I understand

15:14.147 --> 15:16.316
why competitive pricing
is important.

15:16.316 --> 15:19.819
I just don't really think
that pricing is the issue here.

15:21.321 --> 15:23.823
So, for reasons that
I will never fully understand,

15:23.823 --> 15:28.195
in my absence, you decided
that you would make yourself

15:28.228 --> 15:32.099
a middleman
inside of your own organization.

15:32.165 --> 15:34.167
My prices,
right at market levels.

15:34.201 --> 15:36.269
I think the problem here is
the prices

15:36.336 --> 15:38.605
that Jerome and Louie
are paying you, right?

15:38.671 --> 15:41.508
So please,
in the future, feel free

15:41.541 --> 15:43.843
not to call me out here
and ask me to cut my margins

15:43.876 --> 15:46.013
and get people that are trying
