(sighs)

36:17.909 --> 36:19.077
(pops)

36:20.412 --> 36:22.781
Where you going? Come on.

36:22.814 --> 36:25.917
(laughs) We got to celebrate
getting that proposal in, honey.

36:25.917 --> 36:27.953
Mm-hmm.

36:27.986 --> 36:29.588
* We got them files in... *

36:29.621 --> 36:31.923
You want to dance with me.

36:31.957 --> 36:33.925
* They wanted thousands *

36:33.959 --> 36:36.127
* Oh, back, back, back, back *

36:36.161 --> 36:38.630
* We gave them millions. *

36:41.767 --> 36:44.202
Okay. All right.

36:44.270 --> 36:47.205
-Who do I need to beat up?
-(chuckles)

36:47.273 --> 36:50.141
I'm a pregnant lawyer,
pretty much un-convictable.

36:50.175 --> 36:52.278
And we both know I got hands.

36:52.311 --> 36:54.646
(both laugh)

36:54.680 --> 36:56.615
Come on, talk to me.

36:56.648 --> 36:58.450
Is this because of Teddy?

36:58.450 --> 37:00.986
Nah, nah. It's just...

37:01.019 --> 37:03.121
just a lot of tension, you know.

37:03.121 --> 37:04.623
A lot going on.

37:05.624 --> 37:08.627
Do you wanna...

37:08.627 --> 37:10.962
Uh, I'm not in the mood
to meditate or cleanse,

37:10.996 --> 37:12.998
anything like that, V.

37:13.031 --> 37:14.633
...have sex?

37:14.666 --> 37:16.635
You release some dopamine
that way.

37:16.635 --> 37:18.304
(both laugh softly)

37:21.340 --> 37:23.309
-Rain check.
-Hmm.

37:23.342 --> 37:25.243
-But I appreciate you.
-(chuckles)

37:25.311 --> 37:26.812
-And everything you do.
-Mm-hmm.

37:28.046 --> 37:31.750
-Excuse me, Franklin.
-Wanda?

37:31.817 --> 37:34.320
Hey, uh, sorry
to mess up your happy hour.

37:34.353 --> 37:37.323
Franklin, you think
we could talk for a second?

37:40.826 --> 37:43.495
-What's up?
-Okay.

37:43.529 --> 37:46.832
So, I was eavesdropping
at the house the other night--

37:46.865 --> 37:48.934
not even gonna lie, my bad--

37:49.000 --> 37:51.036
but I thought
I heard you say something

37:51.069 --> 37:53.171
about Betty having
water on her knees?

37:53.171 --> 37:55.674
Can't walk up all the stairs
to collect the rent?

37:55.674 --> 37:57.208
Well, I'm not sure if you know,
but...

37:57.242 --> 37:59.545
I used to run track at Jordan.

37:59.578 --> 38:02.448
-I didn't know that.
-Okay, well, I, um, grew up

38:02.514 --> 38:04.716
doing construction work
with my daddy, too.

38:04.750 --> 38:07.519
So handiwork?
Pssh, ain't no thing.

38:07.553 --> 38:09.355
I mean, shit,
you could ask Leon.

38:09.355 --> 38:11.523
One time I had to fix
his mama's dryer, right?

38:11.523 --> 38:13.959
No wrench, all hands.

38:14.025 --> 38:15.894
Last time
I went in the projects,

38:15.927 --> 38:18.364
dryer still blowing.

38:18.364 --> 38:20.599
You asking for a job, Wanda?

38:21.900 --> 38:24.970
Look, I need something else
in my life.

38:25.036 --> 38:27.473
Okay?
This-this scraping-by shit...

38:27.539 --> 38:30.075
I don't know how much longer
I can do it.

38:30.108 --> 38:31.910
(sighs):
Uh...

38:33.111 --> 38:35.213
-All right, all right.
-Okay. Thank you so much.

38:35.246 --> 38:36.415
Ooh, thank you, thank you,
Franklin.

38:36.448 --> 38:37.883
Look, take as much time
as you need.

38:37.916 --> 38:39.217
But not too much time.

38:39.250 --> 38:40.719
-Bitches is broke.
-(chuckles)

38:40.752 --> 38:42.754
-Thank you.
-All right.

39:01.607 --> 39:03.609
FRANKLIN:
How'd it go in Inglewood?

39:03.642 --> 39:05.977
Settled everything
without firing a shot.

39:07.245 --> 39:09.314
Long as it's settled.

39:12.484 --> 39:14.586
You talk to Teddy?

39:14.620 --> 39:16.254
(sighs)
Yeah.

39:18.123 --> 39:19.958
-And?
-You know, honestly,

39:19.991 --> 39:21.593
I'm tired of talking
about this shit, Louie.

39:22.794 --> 39:24.362
We about to start
this shit up again?

39:24.430 --> 39:26.197
Yes, we are.

39:26.264 --> 39:28.366
'Cause they got no idea
the shit we going through

39:28.434 --> 39:30.368
out in the street, and you
won't let me talk to him,

39:30.436 --> 39:32.938
so pardon me if I want to know
what the fuck he said.

39:32.971 --> 39:34.606
-You want to know what he said?
-Yeah.

39:34.606 --> 39:36.107
He said the prices
ain't changing,

39:36.107 --> 39:37.709
'cause the prices
ain't the problem.

39:37.776 --> 39:38.777
-Know what is?
-LOUIE: Hmm?

39:38.777 --> 39:39.811
Y'all two.

39:41.112 --> 39:43.381
Breaking away from me.

39:43.449 --> 39:45.817
-Going out on your own.
-LOUIE: I see.

39:45.851 --> 39:47.385
So you just gonna bend over

39:47.453 --> 39:49.788
-and do whatever he say?
-FRANKLIN (chuckles): No.

39:49.788 --> 39:51.457
But this time he's right.

39:51.457 --> 39:53.224
Look, I gave y'all a chance.

39:53.291 --> 39:55.126
Did this shit
for as long as I could.

39:55.126 --> 39:57.796
But this little experiment,
it's not working.

39:57.796 --> 39:59.998
I'm happy to split the profits
with you all fifty-fifty.

40:01.299 --> 40:02.333
But you got to come home.

40:02.367 --> 40:03.969
Get this operation
under one roof.

40:04.002 --> 40:05.804
No, we ain't doing that.

40:05.804 --> 40:08.474
-Why? Why not?
-Because I don't want
to put my life--

40:08.474 --> 40:11.743
our life-- at risk
for your bullshit-ass decisions.

40:11.810 --> 40:13.979
Is that it?

40:14.012 --> 40:16.582
Or is that you're so sure
that you're so much smarter

40:16.648 --> 40:18.083
than everybody else?

40:18.149 --> 40:19.485
Getting tired of this.

40:19.518 --> 40:20.919
Lions fighting over sheep.

40:20.986 --> 40:23.421
-This between me and him.
-Oh, yeah?

40:23.489 --> 40:25.423
So why don't you
handle it, then?

40:25.491 --> 40:28.026
Boom! That's right.

40:28.059 --> 40:30.361
'Cause I know breaking away
wasn't Jerome's idea.

40:30.395 --> 40:33.499
And I let it go,
'cause you'd been shot,

40:33.532 --> 40:34.833
been through
some traumatic shit.

40:34.833 --> 40:36.702
Hey, you let it go?

40:36.735 --> 40:39.004
Yeah, that's right. For her.

40:39.037 --> 40:41.840
Don't talk
out your goddamn neck, boy.

40:41.840 --> 40:44.510
(laughs) Well,
then maybe you can enlighten me,

40:44.543 --> 40:47.212
Unc, on what the fuck she wants!

40:47.245 --> 40:50.448
Nah. Why don't you ask her
yourself, then?

40:50.516 --> 40:53.218
What would you like,
Queen Louie?

40:53.251 --> 40:54.853
What's gonna make you happy?

40:54.886 --> 40:56.354
'Cause nothing seems to do it
for you.

40:56.354 --> 41:00.225
How about not being
under anybody's thumb, nephew.

41:00.258 --> 41:02.460
FRANKLIN:
Well, I hate to break it to you,

41:02.528 --> 41:04.863
but everybody's got to answer
to somebody. And me?

41:04.863 --> 41:07.465
I answer to the man who may have
disappeared my fucking father,

41:07.533 --> 41:09.635
and who will do the same to us
if we don't move this product.

41:09.701 --> 41:13.038
Now, I don't know about y'all
two, but I'd like to stay alive

41:13.071 --> 41:15.240
long enough
to enjoy what I've made.

41:15.273 --> 41:17.208
So from here on out, I don't
want to hear anything else

41:17.208 --> 41:18.476
about kilos or prices.

41:18.544 --> 41:20.045
Y'all want to go out
on your own? Fine!

41:20.078 --> 41:22.648
But do not for one second
fuck around

41:22.714 --> 41:24.482
with what I got to do
to get mine,

41:24.550 --> 41:27.218
'cause I promise you there is
nothing I'm not prepared to do.

41:31.422 --> 41:32.891
(car door opens)

41:42.233 --> 41:43.902
(engine starts)

43:24.335 --> 43:26.337
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

43:30.876 --> 43:33.511
FRANKLIN: There's a lot
at stake these days.

43:33.578 --> 43:36.514
And I am under
a lot of pressure.

43:36.581 --> 43:38.583
We're glad you got
your own dreams,

43:39.350 --> 43:41.920
but they're not ours.

43:41.953 --> 43:44.522
-(elevator bell dings)
-This empire,
it's gonna crumble.

43:46.257 --> 43:47.592
-(brakes squeal)
-(grunts)

43:50.228 --> 43:52.097
FRANKLIN: I'm gonna do
whatever it takes.

44:00.371 --> 44:01.740
FRANKIE: Get in shape.

44:01.807 --> 44:03.942
-You might have a chance
of living past 60.
-Yes!

44:06.444 --> 44:08.046
(gasps)

44:08.113 --> 44:09.447
-She's so pretty.
-Who's pretty?

44:09.480 --> 44:10.916
Mom, this conversation
is private.

44:10.982 --> 44:14.485
They're all older than me now.
You wouldn't believe it.

44:14.585 --> 44:16.988
Life is a series
of befores and afters.

44:19.124 --> 44:20.391
Okay.

44:20.458 --> 44:23.628
I'm jealous of everybody
who gets to meet you
down the road.

44:23.661 --> 44:25.897
ADLON: FX's
Better Things.

44:25.964 --> 44:28.800
All new, Mondays
at 10:00 on FX.

44:37.909 --> 44:39.510
Here for the do, is it?

44:39.610 --> 44:41.747
I don't--
I don't know what you're saying.

44:47.018 --> 44:48.653
Do I gotta get naked for this?

44:48.686 --> 44:51.857
Nudity isn't required, I think.

44:51.957 --> 44:53.992
[scoffs] I don't know. Europe.

45:02.968 --> 45:04.102
(screams)

45:04.135 --> 45:05.636
WOMAN:
We are not safe here.

45:06.872 --> 45:08.339
We don't really
live in this world.

45:09.140 --> 45:10.041
We feed off of it.

45:11.176 --> 45:13.478
Aliens. Mother of God.

45:14.479 --> 45:16.314
How have you
not gone insane?

45:17.783 --> 45:19.650
Once you sell your soul,
it's gone.

45:20.151 --> 45:21.319
MAN: Boo!

45:21.352 --> 45:22.320
It's breaking
all the rules.

45:22.387 --> 45:23.488
(screams)

45:23.521 --> 45:24.790
And I'm here for that.
